{
  "texts": [
    "This method demonstrates the potential for automating the segmentation of complex fossil structures, although limitations in generalization to other taxa highlight the need for more diverse datasets.",
    "The proposed method represents an important step forward in fossil CT data processing, offering significant improvements in speed and reproducibility, though further work is necessary to ensure broader applicability across paleontological studies.",
    "Lastly, Edie et al. (2023) propose a DL workflow for MicroCT data to separate Bivalve shells from the surrounding calcareous matrix in rock samples.",
    "The use of DL is justified by highlighting that relying solely on material density is insufficient for segmentation in this context.",
    "Whilst DL has significantly advanced the segmentation of bivalve fossils from the matrix in this example, achieving perfect segmentation remains elusive, necessitating manual adjustments to finalize the segmentation process."
  ]
}